- `ITEM_PREMIUM`: the name says "premium per item type" but these values are actually final computed premiums (including 10% surcharge and 5G fee), not base premiums — the name is misleading. However, this is a hardcoded approximation table that will be replaced when we implement real computation; renaming to `ITEM_TOTAL_PREMIUM` would be marginally more accurate but adds noise. The real fix is computing from base premiums. I'll keep it for now as the table's days are numbered.
- `processScenario`, `results`, `step`, `itemType`: all clear → keep

